  "description": "OSTINATO coupling. Breathy, chant-like voice with OSTINATO's rhythmic patterns modulating the breath component and sync timing simultaneously. The voice breathes in time with the rhythm — inhale as sync drops, exhale as it builds. O-to-U vowel morph gives it a ceremonial, ritualistic quality. The choir becomes a breathing circle.",
